from pyspark.ml.evaluation import MulticlassClassificationEvaluator

%pyspark
from pyspark.ml.classification import RandomForestClassifier, LogisticRegression, DecisionTreeClassifier

rf = RandomForestClassifier(labelCol = 'label', featuresCol = 'features')
pipeline = Pipeline(stages=[rf])

model = pipeline.fit(trainingData)

# Make predictions.
predictions = model.transform(testData)

%pyspark
TP = int(predictions.select("label", "prediction").where((col("label") == 0) & (col('prediction') == 0)).count())
TN = int(predictions.select("label", "prediction").where((col("label") == 1) & (col('prediction') == 1)).count())
FP = int(predictions.select("label", "prediction").where((col("label") == 0) & (col('prediction') == 1)).count())
FN = int(predictions.select("label", "prediction").where((col("label") == 1) & (col('prediction') == 0)).count())
total = int(predictions.select("label").count())

print("accuracy = %f" % ((TP + TN) / total))
print("precision = %f" % ((TP + FP) / total))
print("recall = %f" % ((TP + FN) / total))
